==English==

===Etymology===
: from Middle French "''blond''" (masculine); "''blonde''" (feminine).

=== Noun ===
''(UK)'' '''blond'''
#a person of fair skin and hair (usually spelled "''blonde''" when referring to a woman).
#a [[pale]] [[golden]] [[brown]] [[colour]].

